Self-inquiry is simple. It only asks you to pay careful attention to what is true and real.

I have two songs. When they were about four, they both went through a phase of having nightmares. I would go into the room. Two small eyes blinked at me from the corner.

"What's the problem?" I'd ask.

"Daddy, there's a monster in the room." Now, I had more than one choice of how to respond... but the only real solution I ever found was to have a good look. Under the bed, in the closet, behind the curtains.

Eventually my sons would let out a deep sigh, smile at me, and fall back to sleep. The problem was not solved, but dissolved. It was never real in the first place, but it took investigation to make it a reality.
