Four Zen pupils who were studying meditation had promised to observe a rule of silence for seven days. On the first day all were silent. The meditation session had begun well, but when night came and the oil lamps were burning dimly, one of the pupils finally could not help himself and said, "Someone should fix those lamps!"
The second pupil was shocked to hear him speak and cautioned him: "We are not supposed to say a word."
"You idiots!" said the third pupil, "now you've both spoken."
"I am the only one who has not talked," proclaimed the fourth pupil.
