When Nasrudin was asked to speak at the mosque, he went up front and asked: "Oh people, do you know what I have come to tell you?"
"No," the crowd answered.
"If you don't know what I have come to tell you, then you are too ignorant to undertand what I was going to say," Nasrudin replied, and walked out.
But the people, yearning for his wisdom, invited him back the next week.
This time, when Nasrudin asked if they knew what he was going to say, the congregation answered, "Yes!"
"Very good," Nasrudin replied, "then I don't have to waste your time," and he walked out again.
The people invited him back a third time. When Nasrudin asked if they knew what he was going to say, half of the congregation said yes and half said no.
"Very good," said Sasrudin. "Those who know should tell those who don't, and I'll be on my way."
