One monk who was scruplulous all his life about keeping the precepts was wlaking home at night and he stepped on something that made a squishing sound. He imagined that he had stepped on an egg-bearing fron, and this caused him no end of distress and alarm. That night when he finally fell asleep he dreamed that hundereds of frogs came to him, demanding hiss life.

The next morning he set out to see where he had walked, and discoved that he had stepped on a rotting eggplant. At that moment he realized the ture meaning of the idea that there is no objective world. And he finally understood how to practice zazen.
