A master and his attendant were traveling, and stopped at an inn. The master went to his room to practice zazen, and to continue to work on the koan: "What is Buddha?"
Chao-chou responded: "A cypress tree in the garden."
Before going to bed, the attendant knocked on the master's door to check on him. There was no response. The attendant opened the door and peeked in, and beheld a massive tree rooted in the center of the room.
