--- Zen saying
%
The person who, being really on the Way, falls upon hard times in the world, will not, as a consequence, turn to that friend who offers him refuge and comfort and encourages their old self to surivive. Rather, he will seek out someone who will faithfully and inexorably help him to risk himself, so that he may endure the difficulty and pass courageously through it. Only to the extent that a person exposes himself over and over again to annihilation, can that which is indestructibnle be found within them. In this daring lies dignitity and the spirit of true awakening.
--- Karlfried Durckheim
%
Once when Takusan was sitting, Sekito saw him and asked: "What are you doing here?"
Yakuasan said, "I'm not doing anything."
Sekito said, "Then you are just sitting idly."
"If I were sitting idily, that would be doing something," Yakusan said.
"You said you are not doing anything," Sekito said. "What is is that you aren't doing?"
"Even tohe saints don't know," said Yakusan.
